<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.ResourceArrayId" Title="ResourceArrayId enumeration" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    ResourceArrayId
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>ResourceArrayId</TypeRef> enumeration is an opaque token identifying a resource array binding reflected from an <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IShaderProgram">IShaderProgram</PageRef>. It is used when binding <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IDataArray">IDataArray</PageRef> and <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.ITexelArray">ITexelArray</PageRef> resources.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        ID values are renderer-generated tokens. Applications should obtain them from shader reflection methods rather
        than constructing arbitrary values.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Members">
    <EnumMemberList>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="Null">
        Indicates that no matching resource array binding was found or that no resource array slot is selected.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
    </EnumMemberList>
  </Section>
